> Enter root mode :

	$ sudo -i

> Install Node.js (v6.3.0 for now) :

	# apt-get update
	# apt-get upgrade -y
	# curl -sL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_6.x | sudo -E bash -
	# apt-get install nodejs -y
	# node -v; npm -v   # To check correct installation

> Create & add SSH Key to GitHub.com;

	# ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -C "ahs502@gmail.com"
	# eval "$(ssh-agent -s)"
	# ssh-add ~/.ssh/id_rsa
	# cat ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub

	Copy the key to your GitHub.com SSH Keys.

> Install some deb packages :

	# apt-get install -y mc build-essential

> Install some npm packages :

	# npm install -g gulp bower express express-generator

> Install Python 2.7.12 : (See: http://tecadmin.net/install-python-2-7-on-ubuntu-and-linuxmint/#)

	# apt-get install -y checkinstall
	# apt-get install -y libreadline-gplv2-dev libncursesw5-dev libssl-dev libsqlite3-dev tk-dev libgdbm-dev libc6-dev libbz2-dev
	# cd /usr/src
	# wget https://www.python.org/ftp/python/2.7.12/Python-2.7.12.tgz
	# tar xzf Python-2.7.12.tgz
	# rm Python-2.7.12.tgz
	# cd Python-2.7.12
	# sudo ./configure
	# sudo make altinstall
	# python2.7 -V   # Check version
	# cd

> Install node-gyp : (See: https://github.com/nodejs/node-gyp)

	# npm install -g node-gyp
	# node-gyp --python /usr/src/Python-2.7.12/python
	# npm config set python /usr/src/Python-2.7.12/python
	
> Install Cloud9 SDK :

	# git clone git://github.com/c9/core.git c9sdk
	# cd c9sdk/
	# scripts/install-sdk.sh

> Clone my project :

	# git clone git@github.com:ahs502/ahs502-nodapp.git

> Setup git :

	# git config --global user.name "Hessam A Shokravi"
	# git config --global user.email "ahs502@gmail.com"
	# git config --list   # To check the results

> Install project packages :

	# cd ~/ahs502-nodapp/
	# sudo npm install

	Install semantic-ui using 'gulp install' in folder lib/semantic/ first,
	Then, disable Google fonts like described earlier.

> Setup bind9 :: (See: BIND9.log)

    # apt-get install -y bind9
    # gulp bind9

> Install nginx : (See: NGINX.log)

    # apt-get install -y nginx   # It needs port 80 to be free !
    # gulp nginx

> Start Cloud9 SDK :

	# screen -R c9
	# ahs502-nodapp/bin/c9sdk-start-ide.sh
	
	Then press <Ctrl+A> then <Ctrl+D> to detach from this new session.
	After that you can use 'screen -r c9' To re-attach that session.

> Install MongoDB : (See: http://www.tutorialspoint.com/articles/how-to-install-mongodb-on-ubuntu-16-04)

	# apt-key adv --keyserver hkp://keyserver.ubuntu.com:80 --recv EA312927
	# echo "deb http://repo.mongodb.org/apt/ubuntu trusty/mongodb-org/3.2 multiverse" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/mongodb-org-3.2.list
	# apt-get update
	# apt-get install -y --allow-unauthenticated mongodb-org
	# nano /etc/systemd/system/mongodb.service   # Paste the following lines :
===============================================================================
[Unit]
Description=High-performance, schema-free document-oriented database
After=network.target

[Service]
User=mongodb
ExecStart=/usr/bin/mongod --quiet --config /etc/mongod.conf

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
	# systemctl start mongodb
	# systemctl status mongodb
	# systemctl enable mongodb

